name: Bali Handara Gate
address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: It is an excellent place for Instagram worth photo opportunities. Other than that, there is very little to do here. Do take note that you have to pay for a ticket for your photo to be taken by the on-site photographers. The payment is small but the wait can take up to 45 minutes depending on the crowd. Heading into the gates will bring you to a 5 star golf resort after a short drive.
review 2: Nice place for taking a photo. Depending on the time of day, it can be busy, meaning it will take a long time before it is your turn. There are no toilets available. If you are short on time, the staff who arranges everything can help you to skip the line and take your photo earlier. Just a matter of asking them nicely.
review 3: Go there in the morning because it gets crowded. I‚Äôve waited 1hour for 20 people before me to take some photos. You pay an entrance fee and you also pay in cash for the photos if you want to take some with the gate. There is no place buy refreshments so keep that in mind to bring water with you while you wait. Nice photos result if you‚Äôre willing to wait.
review 4:
Waste of Time.

This is just a Gate of Handara Golf and Resort.

Vehicles are regularly passing.

You have to wait like a whole day if you don't reach by 9-10 am.

You can Happily skip this without any regrets.
review 5: Wonder how this spot even got listed on the first place amidst popular bali locations. It's a private golf property whose entrance resembles the popular gateway of heaven, and hence folks line up to get their photos clicked. It has a parking fee, and an entrance fee, just for this photo spot. And the guard whistles to drive you away if you try to click a photo without entering. Can be totally skipped, just like the Lempuyang temple if you are not just looking for a photo.

name: Leon's Strawberry
address: Jl. Raya Pancasari, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1:
Absolutely worth the 2-hour drive to visit this strawberry farm. Everyone was incredibly friendly.

Entrance fee is 15k/person, which includes a refreshing strawberry juice. Picking your own strawberries is at 50k/kg and I managed to get many large, delicious ones. My friends and I thoroughly enjoyed our experience. Highly recommended for a visit!
review 2: Nice place for strawberry picking... The experience was amazing.. the best strawberry I ever had. Even the juice they provided was out of the world...
review 3: I know this place from tiktok, entry ticket 10k/person, free strawberry juice. The staff is so humble, taste of strawberry is sweet and price is affordable. Recommended
review 4: The second time me and my partner were here. I think among all strawberry picking, so far this is the best farm. My partner is bule so maybe thats why I pay 15k per person entrance and you pay 5000 per one ounce of strawberry. We get bunch 1.3kg only for 60k. Cheapy!! They give you free fresh strawberry juice too. Better come here morning before everyone gets in.
review 5:
Good place, good price, good people! They told us honestly that they don't have much strawberry ready to be picked, so we may decide in advance whether to stop by or not..
They also sell strawberry juice, which is super fresh and tasty even with just a bit addition of sugar

name: Warung Makan Tenten Bamboe
address: Jl. Pancasari - Baturiti, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1:
Visited this place for dinner.
We ordered Fried Chicken and grilled chicken.
We also ordered Fried Chicken rice.
They have different seating areas.
Staff are helpful in selecting the menu.

Overall good
review 2: The place is quaint and cute but not a very posh one. Good for grabbing a quick meal.
review 3:
The private driver that we hire in Bali for this trip took us here for lunch. The place looks gloomy and dark. It has an outdoor and indoor seating areas. There is a rest room, too, conveniently located on the outer seating area. Eventhough from the entrance, the place looks small and dark, but it has a bright and spacious outdoor area.  One can just walk around and enjoy the space there. As it was hot and sunny, we decided to sit in the indoor area to enjoy the fan inside.
We ordered the Nasi Ayam Lalapan and Nasi Goreng ikan masin. As usual the white rice is seperately charged. The food are not tasty or appetising. It is just okay.
There is nothing special here. The staff are friendly and accomodating. It was a quick lunch as we had other places to visit.
review 4:
We always have lunch here until Covid arrived and shut many restaraunts down. Ten Ten Bamboe is now open again. Good quality traditional food and limited Western food available and of course the same friendly staff. Pricing is fair and service excellent. Please give them a go. We always do & never disappointed.
Delicious strawberries avail as well to take home.
review 5: The worst meal I ever had in Bali. They charged a rip-off price for everything, especially 240k + 15% tax and service fee for the crispy duck meal and 90k + 15% for 7 small pieces of calamari. The place was dirty and full of flies. I would nominate this place as a tourist scam recommended by the driver (GALUNG Trans).

name: Moondy Strawberry
address: Pancasari, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: great experience to harvest strawberry by yourself. great place for vacation after from bedugul lake. get better experience with harvesting strawberry in its season from juny to august. recommended as the host is friendly and helpfull
review 2: The best place to pick strawberries, the staff is very friendly. There is no entry ticket, we are not allowed to eat the strawberries from the garden, and can just pick, later we will weigh and pay 50,000/kg for the strawberries, there is strawberry juice which is amazingly delicious, very fresh, the price is also affordable, only 10,000/cup, there are noodles too. There we can also relax by sitting in the gazebo that has been provided, the toilet is also clean. next time will visit here againüòçü•∞
review 3: They have the best strawberries.. and very well cared farm, clean‚Ä¶ definitely going back
review 4: The owner was really sweet. Must visit.Thr strawberries tasted great.
review 5:
Cheap and plenty of ripe strawberries.

Place was well maintained.

Recommended!

name: Hotel Pancasari
address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar No.Desa, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: We did not like it. Water heater does not work. Bath water is brown color. Light does not work, everything surely so outdated. Broken glass window, ceeling that about to scrambled down, spider webs go crazy, humid room and dusty interior. No water compliment, even we have to pay for a jar of hot water.. the good thing that they have spacious room.
review 2: definitely a big NO! my team and i were traveling to singaraja and it was very late and this is the only available hotel with 3 rooms. We were shock to see inside of the rooms. The other room was haunted, it's like abandoned hotel, very awful gave us goosebump. It's too bad that actually it has beautiful scenery and so tranquil but the room is just worst. Ohh we also just realized in the morning that this hotel located just across the cemetery.
review 3: Rats and cockroaches in the room. Heater doesn't work. You can hear the other rooms like there is no walls, front door don't close... It would be nice to maintain this hotel... We left.
review 4:
The Concept good , but Need a big renovation. Big room ,but Dark, stinky, old and already broken.
Dont wanna stay in there.
review 5: Stunning landscape and athmospere. Also friendly manager.

name: Waroeng Glory Pizza
address: Jalan Raya Denpasar - Singaraja, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81162, Indonesia
review 1:
Good calm atmosphere,

Eat at your own time

We ate pizza, burger and Boba for my kid

Since we were vegetarian their veg pizza was very good

All things freshly made

Staff was very friendly

Quantity was adequate for us
Medium pizza was of medium size we get everywere
review 2:
I recently visited Waroeng Glory Pizza Bedugul and I must say, it was an absolute delight! The food was simply scrumptious - the burgers were juicy and packed with flavor.

What made the experience even more special was meeting the kind owner and his beautiful family. They were incredibly hospitable and went out of their way to make sure we had a wonderful dining experience. It's clear that they take great pride in their restaurant and are dedicated to providing their customers with the best possible service.

The ambiance of the restaurant is cozy and inviting, with a rustic feel that adds to the overall charm. The staff were friendly and attentive, making sure we had everything we needed throughout our meal.

Overall, I had a fantastic experience at Waroeng Glory Pizza Bedugul and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for delicious food and great service.
review 3:
We were tired and hungry, we chose this place based on good reviews, but were disappointed. The portions are very small, even my child didn‚Äôt get enough.

They take a long time to cook and when my son and I had already eaten, my husband waited another 15 minutes for his dish. The food was certainly delicious, but for this price it was not enough; we did not expect that 1 portion of spaghetti was about half the size of a normal portion.

I don't recommend this place
review 4: Amazing pizza for great price. We bought a medium take away pizza for two people. The owner was so kind and he speaks really good english. This place is a must if you‚Äôre in the zone and want pizza. I would repeat without doubt!!
review 5:
We found exactly what we were craving here. It‚Äôs not what you would find in Italy, but it‚Äôs good for the area.
The vegetarian one has a lot of corn, maybe ask for less if you‚Äôre not a fan.

name: Asta Rasa (warung makan)
address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: The worst spaghetti bolognese I have ever eaten in my life. I am surprised that ratings here are so good üò≥ three times had to change the order because they didn‚Äôt have ingredients. 1 hour of waiting for food. On the photo steak ü•©
review 2:
A great place to eat after visiting Bali Handara Gate and Bali Handara Golf Course. The place has a good parking spot, so you don't need to worry about parking (which is quite hard in the area).

Additionally we were quite surprised with the food, unexpectedly it was quite good, considering the price is not expensive. Will visit again next time.

We ordered the Bebek Goreng (their speciality), and the sauce was really nice, but it was quite spicy, if you don't like spicy you probably want to try the other menu
review 3:
Excellent place to eat when you are visiting Handara gate. Food was beyond our expectations, taste, quality and presentation that too with a very affordable price range.
The staffs were so polite and they do speak English.
We had nasi goreng, fluffy pancake with vannilla icecream, tipat cantok and hot tea.
review 4:
Edit: They don't do pancakes anymore. :(

You wouldn't believe it. Best pancake of Bali so far. Yes here, far away form any town, somewhere nowhere. I'm not kidding you.

The rest of the food....as you would think it is....
review 5: The best place to try local food. I recommend samosa, very tasted if you like spicy food. The people is very friendly

name: Asta Wilangun Giri Mas Pancasari
address: P5W5+8F4, Pancasari, Sukasada, Buleleng Regency, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: We were pleasantly surprised at this stop along the road. They served delicious chicken soup for my son without spice ( he doesn‚Äôt eat spicy) my vegetarian nasi goreng had a subtly different flavor that was pleasant. Also, a lovely garden atmosphere and small park for kids.
review 2:
Very affordable pricing
Cozy place
Coffe latte is the best
Love all the menu's
review 3: These guys make awesome espresso based coffee from local beans which are roasted in the village. Well worth a visit.
review 5: My favourite coffee shop in Sukasada‚ù§Ô∏è Cappuccino is great

address: P5W5+93W, Jl. Raya Denpasar - Bedugul, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: It was a nice and cheep! Love it!

name: Gading Restaurant
address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: We sat upstairs on the terrace, it was nice and not as loud next to the traffic. Nasi Goreng was delicious and very cheap. Would eat here again.
review 2: Wow! The food was just incredible good!!!

address: Jl. Raya Singaraja-Denpasar, Pancasari, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: Very nice farm! We have been here 3 times. The owner is very friendly. Recommendation!

review 1: Trying to find shelter from rain then found this place. Must try the pork satay and rawon. The satay is delicious and juicy. The rawon is nice too but the meat were to few. But for the price offered, it really worth it. We order 2 rawon, 1 satay and 2 pork skin cracker. Pay only 32K.
review 2: Absolutely yummy. Stopped to get takeaway bintang but the sate cooking smell made us park and go for a snack - YUM üòã
review 3: The pork satay is juiciy and tender, and the soup is refreshing, spice and herby. Moderate portions, suitable for brunch
review 4: Just randomly stopped at this stall for lunch and was feeling satisfied with the pork satay (sate babi) and soup (rowon).

review 2: Personnel was a bit unfriendly. Tons of flies. Very bad hygiene. Chicken tasted so so. Chicken Burger however had a bun that had already a bite out of it, disgusting. Didn‚Äôt even taste like chicken. Wouldn‚Äôt recommend at all.
